<h2>Purpose</h2>
<p>
  Phase 2 of the <a href="/backlog/315-competitive-coverage-gap-analysis-program/">competitive coverage
  gap-analysis program</a> (<a href="/backlog/346-capability-extraction-normalization-schema/">#346</a>):
  the <strong>normalized capability matrix</strong> extracted from the
  <a href="/research/benchmark-corpus/">benchmark corpus</a>. Each row is one capability the corpus
  exposes, deduped across sources into a stable <code>id</code> (Material &ldquo;Menu&rdquo;, Fluent
  &ldquo;Menu&rdquo;, Radix &ldquo;Dropdown Menu&rdquo; &rarr; one <code>menu</code> capability). Phase 3
  (<a href="/backlog/347-capability-mapping-gap-detection/">#347</a>) joins each row to a Web Everything
  entity and labels coverage. Data: <code>src/_data/benchmarkCapabilities.json</code>; this page renders
  from it.
</p>

<h2>Extraction method</h2>
<p>{{ benchmarkCapabilities.method.howRead }}</p>
<p><strong>Dedup:</strong> {{ benchmarkCapabilities.method.dedup }}</p>
<p><strong>Scope (first pass):</strong> {{ benchmarkCapabilities.method.scope }}</p>
<p><strong>Reproducibility:</strong> {{ benchmarkCapabilities.method.reproducibility }}</p>

<h2>The matrix</h2>
<p>
  <code>ubiquity</code> is a coarse cross-corpus signal (universal / common / partial / rare-emerging);
  <code>notableIn</code> flags standout implementations; <code>nativeAnchorHint</code> records the native
  API/element a capability plausibly maps to &mdash; the input phase 3 uses to keep gap detection
  <em>native-first</em>.
</p>
{% for k in benchmarkCapabilities.kinds %}
<h3>{{ k.label }}</h3>
<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Capability</th><th>Family</th><th>Ubiquity</th><th>Native anchor</th><th>Summary</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for c in benchmarkCapabilities.capabilities %}{% if c.kind == k.id %}
    <tr>
      <td><strong>{{ c.label }}</strong></td>
      <td>{{ c.family }}</td>
      <td>{{ c.ubiquity }}</td>
      <td>{% if c.nativeAnchorHint %}{{ c.nativeAnchorHint }}{% else %}&mdash; (no native anchor){% endif %}</td>
      <td>{{ c.summary }}</td>
    </tr>
    {% endif %}{% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% endfor %}
